Follow PEP 0008 -- Style Guide for Python Code
https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/

Important Points:

* Indent with exactly 4 spaces. No Tabs allowed.

* Limit all lines to a maximum of 79 characters.
* Surround top-level function and class definitions with two blank lines.
* Method definitions inside a class are surrounded by a single blank line.
* Avoid trailing whitespace anywhere.

* Imports should usually be on separate lines.
* Imports on top of the file.
* No wildcard imports.

* One space after block comment and comment to indented too.
* Use inline comments sparingly.
* Write docstrings for all public modules, functions, classes, and methods. 

* Module names is all-lowercase.
* Class names with CamelCase.
* Function names all-lowercase with underscores.
* Use self for the first argument to instance methods.
* Use cls for the first argument to class methods.
* Constants in all capital.
